lass=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3dab990 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"3dab990\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Basics<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Most Common Exocrine Pancreatic Neoplasia (85-90%)<\/li><li>4<sup>th<\/sup> Most Common CA-Related Death<\/li><li>Most Common Location: <strong>Main Duct<\/strong> &amp; Head<\/li><li>Spreads Through Lymphatics<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Associated Mutations<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><strong>K-Ras<\/strong> (Most Common)<\/li><li>p16 (CDKN2A)<\/li><li>p53<\/li><li>BRCA1\/2<\/li><li>MLH1<\/li><li>ATM<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Risk Factors<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><strong>Tobacco #1<\/strong><\/li><li>Obesity<\/li><li>Diabetes<\/li><li>Chronic Pancreatitis<\/li><li>BRCA2<\/li><li>FAP<\/li><li>Cystic Fibrosis<\/li><li>History of Cholecystectomy<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Subtypes<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Adenosquamous<\/li><li>Colloid (Best Prognosis)<\/li><li>Hepatoid<\/li><li>Medullary<\/li><li>Anaplastic, Colloid, etc.<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Presentation<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Symptoms:<ul><li><strong>Jaundice<\/strong> \u2013 Most Common Presenting Symptom<\/li><li>Fatigue<\/li><li>Weight Loss<\/li><li>Anorexia<\/li><li>Abdominal Pain<\/li><li>Nausea &amp; Vomiting<\/li><li>Diarrhea<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Courvoisier Sign<\/em> \u2013 Painless Palpable Gallbladder with Jaundice<ul><li>Indicates Malignancy (Pancreas\/Gallbladder)<\/li><li>*Historical Sign with Limited Utility and Many Exceptions<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Trousseau\u2019s Sign<\/em> \u2013 Unexplained Superficial Migratory Thrombophlebitis<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Diagnosis<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Initial Imaging: CT (85% Sensitive)<\/li><li>If CT Positive:<ul><li>If Resectable: Surgery<ul><li><strong>No Bx Needed<\/strong> \u2013 High False Negative<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>If Appears Borderline\/Unresectable\/Mets: EUS-Guided Bx<ul><li>To Guide Chemotherapy<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Vascular Invasion Unclear: <strong>EUS<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>If CT Negative but High Suspicion: ERCP (90% Sensitive)<\/li><li>Tumor Marker: CA 19-9<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Unresectable Definition<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Invades Celiac Axis &gt; 50%<\/li><li>Invades SMA &gt; 50%<\/li><li>Contact with the Most Proximal SMA or SMV Branches<\/li><li>Invasion of SMV or Portal Vein <strong>if Unable to Reconstruct<\/strong><\/li><li>Lymph Nodes Beyond the Field of Resection (Such as Celiac or SMA Nodal Systems)<\/li><li>Mets<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-5634833\" data-id=\"5634833\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b951a3a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"b951a3a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-10495 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Pancreas-Adenocarcinoma.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"467\" height=\"177\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Pancreas-Adenocarcinoma.jpg 467w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Pancreas-Adenocarcinoma-300x114.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 467px) 100vw, 467px\" \/><\/p><p>Pancreatic Adenocarcinoma of the Tail <sup>1<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\